column5: Email from Jim! So if you depend on Jim for winter supplies, you'll have to shop short of town at Gramps I guess.
Ill be dropping in on our way to camp next time!
I'm sure he'll appreciate if you buy something toooo TJ ! lol  He had some nice tackle in there when I went in to say goodbye in late September.
to bad he did not have that sale on in sept. i would have bought the store lol
LOL ONLY PROBLEM BUYING THAT WE WOULD NEVER GET ANY WORK DONE WE WOULD BE OUT FISHING ALL THE TIME LOL BUT WHEELS ARE TURNING A BIT HERE HMMMMMMMMMMM
Too bad about the lack of sales. When i was up 2 years ago for 2 weeks the place was great. Very friendly and they gave me a ton of info about the lake. I spent a lot of $$$ there.
That's too bad he'll be closed for the winter...he's the man!  Ah well...thanks for the post Wayne.
thats very sad news wayne..i guess gramps will be my stop in spot..
Nice fella.  Economy probably kicked that town in the head this past summer.  His business would be first to suffer the ache.
